{
  "texts": [
    "The iteration stops after the vocabulary reaches a predetermined size.",
    "Vocabulary finalization the final vocabulary will have symbols representing individual bytes, common byte sequences, and multi-byte tokens.",
    "The procedure finalizes the vocabulary by adding non-linguistic tokens such as [PAD] and [UNK] to accommodate padding and unknown tokens, respectively, as well as other special tokens to deal with other situations.",
    "Post-tokenization convert the pre-tokenized input corpus by replacing tokens with their matching n-grams in the final vocabulary.",
    "Intuition: Iterative merging grows the initial list of unique symbols by including newly merged symbols that appear most often in the TFD."
  ]
}